olive oil
2 potatoes
1 packet Slow-Cooked Beef Brisket
1 bag Slaw Mix
1 packet mayonnaise
1 drizzle white wine vinegar
1 bag baby spinach leaves
1 sachet Aussie Spice Blend
1 packet BBQ sauce

• Preheat oven to 240°C/220°C fan-forced. Cut potato into bite-sized chunks.
• Place potato on a lined oven tray. Sprinkle over Aussie spice blend, drizzle with olive oil, season with salt and toss to coat.
• Spread out evenly, then roast until tender, 20-25 minutes.

• Place slow-cooked beef brisket in a baking dish. Pour liquid from the packaging over the beef.
• Cover tightly with foil and bake for 12 minutes. Turn beef, then re-cover with foil and bake until heated through and liquid has slightly reduced, a further 12 minutes.

• In a medium bowl, combine baby spinach leaves, slaw mix, mayonnaise and a drizzle of vinegar. Season.
• Slice beef brisket.
• Divide spiced roast potato, brisket and slaw between plates. Top beef with BBQ sauce to serve. Enjoy!